  <!-- ========== 16 — HOW TO USE DOCUMENTATION ========== -->
  <section class="resources-tips section-padding" aria-label="Tips for using documentation effectively">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="resources-category__header">
        <span class="section-number">16</span>
        <h2 class="resources-category__title">How to Use Documentation Effectively</h2>
        <p class="resources-category__desc">
          Reading documentation is a skill that improves with practice. Understanding how to navigate, search, and extract
          relevant information efficiently makes you more productive.
        </p>
      </div>

      <ol class="resources-tips-list">
        <li class="resources-tip">
          <span class="resources-tip__number">TIP 01</span>
          <h3 class="resources-tip__title">Start with Getting Started Guides</h3>
          <p class="resources-tip__desc">
            Begin with official tutorials and quickstarts before diving into API references. These introductory materials
            establish mental models and common patterns that make detailed documentation more comprehensible.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li class="resources-tip">
          <span class="resources-tip__number">TIP 02</span>
          <h3 class="resources-tip__title">Bookmark Frequently Referenced Sections</h3>
          <p class="resources-tip__desc">
            Maintain browser bookmarks or notes for documentation sections you reference repeatedly. Common targets include
            API references, configuration options, and migration guides.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li class="resources-tip">
          <span class="resources-tip__number">TIP 03</span>
          <h3 class="resources-tip__title">Understand the Documentation Structure</h3>
          <p class="resources-tip__desc">
            Each documentation site has its own organization. Spend time understanding the structure before searching.
            Typical sections include guides, API references, examples, and release notes.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li class="resources-tip">
          <span class="resources-tip__number">TIP 04</span>
          <h3 class="resources-tip__title">Read Release Notes and Changelogs</h3>
          <p class="resources-tip__desc">
            Release notes document changes, new features, deprecations, and breaking changes. Understanding deprecation timelines
            prevents surprises during upgrades.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li class="resources-tip">
          <span class="resources-tip__number">TIP 05</span>
          <h3 class="resources-tip__title">Use Documentation Search Effectively</h3>
          <p class="resources-tip__desc">
            Most documentation sites have powerful search. Learn search syntax and keyboard shortcuts. Search for specific
            function names, error messages, or concepts.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li class="resources-tip">
          <span class="resources-tip__number">TIP 06</span>
          <h3 class="resources-tip__title">Check Documentation Version</h3>
          <p class="resources-tip__desc">
            Ensure documentation matches your installed version. Version mismatches are a common source of frustration
            when APIs change between releases.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li class="resources-tip">
          <span class="resources-tip__number">TIP 07</span>
          <h3 class="resources-tip__title">Read Beyond Your Immediate Problem</h3>
          <p class="resources-tip__desc">
            When solving a specific issue, read surrounding documentation sections. Context helps understand why APIs work
            the way they do and reveals better approaches.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li class="resources-tip">
          <span class="resources-tip__number">TIP 08</span>
          <h3 class="resources-tip__title">Experiment with Examples</h3>
          <p class="resources-tip__desc">
            Type out and run documentation examples yourself. Don't just read them. Hands-on experimentation builds deeper
            understanding than passive reading.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li class="resources-tip">
          <span class="resources-tip__number">TIP 09</span>
          <h3 class="resources-tip__title">Contribute to Documentation</h3>
          <p class="resources-tip__desc">
            When you find unclear documentation or errors, contribute improvements. Most projects accept documentation PRs
            readily. Contributing deepens your own understanding.
          </p>
        </li>
      </ol>
    </div>
  </section>

